The paper deals with the segmentation of brain tumors in MRI data using a semi-automatic approach that relies on computer-assisted segmentation methods. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms and image processing techniques, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) for segmentation, which is another indication of its relevance to these sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals specifically with glioblastoma multiforme (cs.MM), which is a type of brain tumor, and this further supports its relevance to these sub-categories.
